ol#tourbus-demo-1.tourbus-legs
  // INTRO
  li(data-orientation='centered', data-mask='true')
    h2 The PINGR tutorial
    p OK! Let's show you how to use PINGR.
    a.tourbus-next(href='javascript:void(0);') Next: Navigation
  li(data-orientation='centered', data-mask='true')
    h2 Here to help
    p PINGR is here to suggest actions to improve patient care. All of it's suggestions are based on your practice's data.
    a.tourbus-next(href='javascript:void(0);') Next: Navigation
  li(data-orientation='centered', data-mask='true')
    h2 You can help PINGR
    p Your input improves PINGR over time. By giving a thumb_down you help PINGR's suggestions for all users
    a.tourbus-next(href='javascript:void(0);') Next: Navigation
  li(data-el='.nav.navbar-nav.navbar-right', data-highlight='true', data-orientation='bottom', data-width='400')
    h2 System buttons
    p These buttons are system level buttons. They are used to let you log out, change your password or contact the admins to help you out!
    a.tourbus-next(href='javascript:void(0);') Next: Navigation
  li(data-el='#mainTab', data-highlight='true', data-orientation='bottom', data-width='400')
    h2 Navigation
    p With these buttons you can access other panels in the system. In general you will move from left (overview panel) to right (action plans panel).
    p Press these buttons to take you to a specific part of the system in case you want to go somewhere specific.
    a.tourbus-next(href='javascript:void(0);') Next: The log out button
  li(data-el='#suggs', data-highlight='true', data-orientation='left', data-arrow='10%', data-width='400')
    h2 The log out button.
    p Click this button if you want to log out of the system.
    a.tourbus-stop(href='javascript:void(0);') Done!


